<i>bound noun</i>: 푼 [푼ː] <i>noun</i>: 말장난 [말ː짱난] <br>
<ul>
<li><i>bound noun</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>푼 [푼ː]</dt><br>
<dd>1. pun</dd><br>
<dd>(옛날에) 엽전을 세던 단위.</dd><br>
<dd>(archaic) A bound noun that serves as a unit for counting yeopjeon or brass coins.</dd><br>
<dd>2. (no equivalent expression)</dd><br>
<dd>돈을 세는 단위.</dd><br>
<dd>A bound noun that serves as a unit for counting money.</dd><br>
<dd>3. pun</dd><br>
<dd>비율을 나타내는 단위.</dd><br>
<dd>A bound noun that serves as a unit of proportion.</dd><br>
</li>
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>말장난 [말ː짱난]</dt><br>
<dd>play on words; pun</dd><br>
<dd>실제로 중요한 내용도 없는 쓸데없는 말을 그럴듯하게 하는 것.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of saying something that sounds plausible but actually is not at all important.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>